<br>
Observations on the server in general:<br>
<br>
I think people are adjusting to the lack of clerics, just getting by without them, and getting by without resurrections at higher levels. <br>
<br>
On class stereotypes:<br>
<br>
While there are situations that require the heavy tank/CH combo, I think people take some stuff WAYYY too seriously the rest of the time. Like what is &quot;expected&quot; of a class. I'm a wussly High Elf, but I still melee when I have the mana because I'm determined to max out my 1HB and defense. I group with friends who trust me to keep them alive, and while they might joke about my meleeing, no one is going to tell me I'm not allowed to, or to &quot;just med&quot;. I also nuke, stun, root, and remove damage shields, and various other stuff. I know how to manage my own aggro, and i know in which situations I DO need to &quot;just med&quot;. <br>
<br>
In short, I have fun, and keep people alive.<br>
<br>
On bards: <br>
<br>
Not going to comment on bard vs. cleric healing, because I think everyone understands the difference (and WHEN the difference matters). But I will say that the addition of a bard turns a good group into a killing machine. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I already run with a warrior, enchanter, and rogue, and we're &quot;nigh indestructible&quot; (apologies to The Tick). But Syllestrae joined us the other night, and it became a nonstop slaughter, with very little meditation necessary.<br>
